he new era where data are abundant and statisticians are scientists. The views represented         here are our own and do not represent the views of Johns Hopkins University, Harvard University or         Dana Farber Cancer Institute.                 We‚Äôll be posting ideas we find interesting, contributing to discussion of science/popular writing,         linking to articles that inspire us, and sharing advice with up-and-coming statisticians.         R Bloggers            R-Bloggers is about empowering bloggers to empower other R users. R-Bloggers. com is a blog         aggregator of content contributed by bloggers who write about R (in English). The site helps         R bloggers and users to connect and follow the ‚ÄúR blogosphere‚Äù.         Towards Data Science            Towards Data Science Inc. is proud to run a publication where independent authors who follow our         rules and guidelines can publish their work, share their knowledge and expertise, and engage a wide         audience on Medium. We love connecting ideas with readers, but we're unable to vet the accuracy of         every contribution ‚Äî so use your best judgment and seek professional advice before taking any action         based on the content on this site.         Statistical Odds and Ends            I am a data scientist with Linkedin's Data Science and Applied Research (DSAR) team. I earned my         PhD in Statistics at Stanford in 2021, advised by Rob Tibshirani. I am interested in all things         statistics, but especially in developing statistical software, understanding how statistical         analyses can impact decision-making more effectively, as well as how statistics is communicated to         the public and in the classroom.                 Short posts about concepts and ideas in statistics and related fields which interest me. This is         also a place for me to clarify some of my thoughts and pen down notes for future reference.         Mathematical Odds and Ends            Short posts about concepts and ideas in mathematics (non-stats) and related fields which interest me.         This is also a place for me to clarify some of my thoughts and pen down notes for future reference.         Beyond Solutions            The goal of this blog is to give you some tools to help you approach math problems in a systematic         manner. We will do this by example. Each blog post will consist of one (or more) math olympiad         problems, followed by my train of thought in working out the solution. The problems in this blog         will range in difficulty but will generally come from competitions for grades 10-12.         Kenneth (Ken) Jee            As the Head of Data Science at Scouts Consulting Group, I spend my work days improving the         performance of athletes and teams by analyzing the data collected on them. I also dabble in         entrepreneurship and content creation. I'm probably best known for my YouTube channel where I         (hopefully) help over 100,000 people navigate the data science landscape.     Artificial intelligence    The Batch					The Batch is an email newsletter published by Dr Andrew Ng's AI education company DeepLearningAI. This 			newsletter delivers the latest news, events, and analyses in AI straight to inboxes. All issues are also			available on DeepLearningAI's official website. 		 		Coursera					Coursera offers courses on AI, including those from DeepLearningAI, Dr Andrew Ng and other top researchers			at top universities and companies worldwide. Most courses offered on Coursera are free and accessible. Those			who pay a price would also receive certification after successfully passing courses, which they can put on			LinkedIn profile and resume. 		 		Baidu Brain (PaddlePaddle AI Studio)					Baidu is the leading Chinese-language search engine that has been investing heavily in AI technology since 			2010. It is one of the pioneers in AI research and the author of the PaddlePaddle deep learning framework. 			The company offers AI courses on its AI Studio platform, aiming at educating billions AI practioners for 			the Chinese nation. 		     DeepMind Blog					DeepMind is a British artificial intelligence research company best known for Go. The company was acquired			by Alphebat, and it continues to conduct cutting-edge research on AI. The company runs a blog in which it 			publishes academic papers on AI and explain how its product offerings and AI technology in general can help			the world. 		 		Open AI					Open AI is a widely successful AI research institution founded by Elon Musk and a few others. The organisation			focuses on cutting-edge AI technology. Similar to DeepMind, it runs a blog where researchers at the firm publish			papers and explain how AI can meaningfully transform the way we work and live. 		 		Open CV					Open CV focuses on the computer vision branch of AI. The platform provides open-source projects around CV and 			offers courses and other resources for global AI researchers and developers to learn CV from experts worldwide. 			It is another awesome resource for AI practitioners. 		 		SenseTime					SenseTime is a Chinese artificial intelligence software company that builds platforms capable of training AI models			with high performance and low cost. The company is research-oriented. It is made up with over 70% employees being 			researchers who conduct research, publish papers, and open-source AI projects. 		 		Scale Exchange					Scale AI is a leading AI company that focuses on data. The company also runs a virtual community called Scale Exchange. 			The Exchange hosts industry practitioners in AI to share thoughts and promote breakthroughs in AI research. 		 Art and design	Inkscape			Inkscape is a free and open-source software for designing clipart art. It is viewed as an equivalent		of Adobe Illustrator. Artists can use this software to design a lot of objects. 	 	GNU Image Manipulation Program			GNU Image Manipulation Program is a free and open-source software for editing photos. It is widely		percieved as the free equivalent of Adobe Photoshop. Click this link to download the software to support		open-source whilst fulfilling your artistic dreams. Stop aiding software piracy today!	 	Krita			Krita is a free and open-source software for art and design. Artists, animators and designers		can use this software to do their personal work. It is highly praised in the open-source and		art and design communities. 	 	OpenToonz			OpenToonz is a free and open-source software for making 2D digital animation. It is recommended by		professors and freelancers as one of the best accessible animation software if you have a low budget 		for your film projects. 	 	Free Sketchbook from Autodesk			Sketchbook is drawing software from Autodesk. After it became an independent company, the software		is no longer free with full feature. The link here; however, links to the original Autodesk software. 		You can get the last version of Sketchbook free from Autodesk's download centre. 	 	&lt;!--responsive footer--&gt;	&lt;!-- &lt;div style= background: #0a314d; color: white; &gt;		&lt;div class= container &gt;			&lt;ul id= footer-items &gt;				&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href= https://www. linkedin. com/in/lizhaozhi &gt;LinkedIn&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;				&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href= https://github. com/mrlizhaozhi &gt;GitHub&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;				&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href= https://www. kaggle. com/mrlizhaozhi/ &gt;Kaggle&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;				&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href= https://public. tableau. com/app/profile/lizhaozhi &gt;Tableau&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;				&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href= https://codepen. io/lizhaozhi &gt;CodePen&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;			&lt;/ul&gt;		&lt;/div&gt;	&lt;/div&gt; --&gt;		&lt;div style= min-height: 200px; background: #0a314d; color: white; &gt;		&lt;div class= container &gt;			&lt;div class= footer-menu &gt;				&lt;!-- &lt;div id= footer-menu-1 &gt;					&lt;ul style= text-align: center; &gt;						&lt;li&gt;&lt;img src= /img/site-log