    "url": "/pages/free-and-open-internet/en-uk/",
    "title": "Free and open Internet",
    "body": "	Other languages: ÁÆÄ‰Ωì‰∏≠Êñá	Why is a free and open Internet important?				The Internet serves as the foundation of the modern digital economy. People live on the Internet as well. Just count how many websites and 		applications you have accessed since the moment you wake up till the moment you lay down. I believe almost no modern citizen can claim that		he has used none. 	 			The Internet needs to be free and open. It is an infrastructure, a platform, but not the content generator or service provider. Keeping this		platform free and open encourages inclusion in the development of the digital economy and society. Those who share and use the content are the 		ones who're in charge of the Internet. Hence, people shall have unhindered access to the Internet, share and consume information and services		as they please. 	 			Simply put, the Internet is a means for sharing knowledge and delivering services for and by the people. It shouldn't be a means that serve the 		interests of a single participant, whether that is the government, an organisation or an individual. A free and open Internet shall serve the 		interests of all, from government to citizens whilst a closed and heavily censored Internet does not. 	 			Read the Determination on Releasing and Receiving Information on the Internet (Chinese only) document		on what the Free and Open Internet (FOI) Initiative stands for. 	 			ON THE TOPIC									January 24, 2022 							Stack Overflow should remove downvotes that discourage the spirit of helping 													Stack Overflow is the world‚Äôs most popular developer community that enables developers worldwide to exchange ideas and find out creative. . . 			 											Follow the #Internet, #Censorship tags to 		learn more on the FOI initiative and the topic. 	 "
