    "title": "On the official closure of my Stack Overflow account: An open letter to Stack Overflow administration and users",
    "body": "2022/02/13 - Dear Stack Overflowers, Thank you for your support. After thorough consideration, I‚Äôve decided to delete my account and leave this platform. Below, I‚Äôm explaining why I made this decision. Stack Overflow has been a popular Q&amp;A platform for global developers to find answers. It‚Äôs many features enable the exchange of ideas and solutions. Like many developers, I visit this forum weekly if not daily; however, I‚Äôm getting tired of its restrictions imposed on newcomers. These restrictions discourage participation. They‚Äôre self-inflicted and should be lifted to make this community more inclusive. Stack Overflow claims that reputation points are optional, but you can‚Äôt do many things without enough points. These include casting votes to solutions, posting comments and even answering certain forum questions. While I understand the motivation is to ensure that no one can spam this platform, I don‚Äôt believe this is a good strategy for meeting this challenge. If developers are unable to share their thoughts simply because they don‚Äôt have enough points (level of addiction) on the platform, they can‚Äôt contribute, and Stack Overflow won‚Äôt be helpful without these contributions. Indeed, many questions posted years ago are left unanswered on Stack Overflow. Even worse, developers can easily lose reputation because someone disagrees with their answers and leaves no valuable feedback. I‚Äôm sick of this rating system. Until Stack Overflow addresses these problems, I will not open an account and contribute to this service. There‚Äôre many other forums where I can find solutions to my questions. Stack Overflow isn‚Äôt the only option; therefore, I won‚Äôt hesitate to reconsider my membership when the service becomes rogue. I‚Äôve written a more detailed post to articulate my concerns on my personal blog website at Stack Overflow should remove downvotes that discourage the spirit of helping. Please give it a read if you agree with me. So long, Stack Overflow, those of you who have been actively contributing to the community, and those who still can‚Äôt because you don‚Äôt have enough addiction to this platform. Best regards, Zhaozhi 13 February 2022 "
