 and will not succeed or merit the same level of respect that global companies like Google, Apple, and Adobe receive. The PRC government censorship is much worse than any U. S. sanction imposed on PRC companies. The censorship rules are harming PRC companies more than any foreign sanction. Many globally successful companies including Twitter, Facebook, and Google are operating without the Chinese market. They‚Äôre successful because they understand and respect the freedoms and rights that are given to every person at birth. There‚Äôre countless PRC citizens bypassing the notorious Great Fire Wall to see what the real world is about on the global platforms that are blocked in the PRC. They look for facts that are censored and inaccessible on PRC platforms. People seek freedoms and rights whenever it is possible not because of voracity; rather, they‚Äôre simply looking for what‚Äôs taken away from them involuntarily. Every human being is entitled with these freedoms and rights. If the CCP doesn‚Äôt lift its restrictions on PRC firms. China, Inc. will never win the market not because of export restrictions but the freedoms-and-rights-killing rules that the Chinese government imposes on them. "
